        "title": "fix(docs): document Codex Computer Use enabled setting",
        "body": "## Summary\n- update the Codex Computer Use Quick setup example to set `plugins.entries.codex.config.computerUse.enabled` to `true`\n- clarify that `enabled: true` is required before pairing it with `autoInstall`\n\n## Why\nThe current Quick setup example only sets `computerUse.autoInstall`. In practice, `/codex computer-use status` can still report Computer Use as disabled/not installed after `/codex computer-use install` until `plugins.entries.codex.config.computerUse.enabled` is explicitly set to `true`.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm -s format:docs:check`\n- `pnpm -s docs:check-mdx docs/plugins/codex-computer-use.md`\n- `pnpm -s lint:docs`\n- `git diff --check`",
